<p>This is “Me” thinking. The more I read and hear on this subject the more I feel collapse is not “If” it is when and how. It is not “where” it will be everywhere. Some areas will see better adjustment out of advantage and luck but when the global system decays either fast or slow the local support systems will be destroyed as we know them everywhere. No area is immune. I would say the “when” will be related to the weakest link. The weakest link now is the global system itself and in particularly the most complex part, the financial system. We currently have financial repression holding the financial system together. Normal market fundamentals have been ditched for centralized economic planning by the central banks. This has just made the system more brittle so when it breaks it will be ugly. It is also destroying the productive base by cannibalization and wealth transfer. These unintended consequences of central bank policy are destroying the social and economic fabric the global system must have to survive. The financial system, being confidence based, can hum along for some time because there is allot of fruit yet to pick in this wealth transfer and cannibalization “BUT” the energy card is next in maybe 6-9yrs. If the finance system manages to hum along and we do not destroy ourselves in war then, the energy card will finish the game. The energy story has been exposed here on this site. In a finite world all systems cycle. Sometimes the system can be forced and a state maintained longer than normal but almost always forcing makes the break in the cycle more severe. In our case it will be ugly because of the population overshoot on a global scale. Folks there is nowhere to go and no plan B’s. The FF forcing meant a huge population overshoot, environmental sterilization, and severe vital resource depletion. Folks I am not talking high grade iron ore resource depletion here I am talking food and water related resources. You know the basic stuff for survival. So the resulting landing somewhere will be without traditional regenerative resources for society to redevelope anything like we have seen in the last 10000 years. This folks will be “THE” bottleneck if not our very extinction. I hope the coffee kicked in and I got overly excited because I do not want this at all.</p>
